genresAdvancedInfo.name: chinese punk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chinese punk is a genre of music that emerged in the late 1970s in China. It is characterized by its fast and aggressive sound, which often incorporates elements of hardcore punk and heavy metal. The lyrics of Chinese punk songs often deal with social and political issues, as well as personal struggles and experiences. Chinese punk bands are known for their energetic live performances and DIY ethos.
